@page "/documentwrite"

<PageTitle>Document.Write</PageTitle>


@* The following inline script will overwrite the entire document's content on an enhanced navigation as the document has already finished loading when the script is executed - therefore data-reload must be disabled *@
<p>Operating successfully for &gt;<script data-reload="false">document.write((new Date().getFullYear())-2000);</script>&lt; years as an independent...</p>


@* The following inline script is safe because it manipulates a specific DOM element *@
<p>Operating successfully for &gt;<span id="years"></span>&lt; years as an independent...</p>
<script data-reload="true">document.getElementById("years").innerHTML = (new Date().getFullYear())-2000;</script>


